        >
          Identity and OAuth2, on your terms.
        </h1>
        <p
          class="mb-7 max-w-[520px] text-[17px] leading-[1.55] text-muted-foreground"
        >
          Olympus is a free identity solution built on Ory Kratos and Hydra. Self-hosted, standards-compliant, no per-seat pricing.
        </p>
        <div
          class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2.5"
        >
          <a
            class="inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-primary px-8 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground no-underline shadow-sm transition-colors hover:bg-primary/90"
            href="#playground"
          >
            Open the playground
          </a>
          <a
            class="inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md border border-input bg-background/80 px-8 text-sm font-medium text-foreground no-underline shadow-sm backdrop-blur-[6px] transition-colors hover:bg-accent"
            href="/docs"
          >
            Read the docs
          </a>
        </div>
        <div
          class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-5 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground"
        >
          <span>
            ✓ Apache 2.0
          </span>
          <span>
            ✓ OIDC · OAuth2 · PKCE
          </span>
          <span>
            ✓ Self-hosted
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div
        style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"
      >
        <div>
          <div
            class="mb-3.5"
          >
            <div
              class="mb-2 inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-muted-foreground"
            >
              <span
                aria-hidden="true"
                class="inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full"
                style="background: rgb(34, 197, 94); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgb(34 197 94 / 0.18);"
              />
              ~60 seconds · zero config
            </div>
            <h3
              class="m-0 text-[19px] font-semibold leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.015em] text-foreground"
            >
              Stand up the whole stack locally with one command.
            </h3>
            <p
              class="mt-1.5 text-[13.5px] leading-[1.55] text-muted-foreground"
            >
              <code
                class="font-mono text-[12.5px] text-foreground"
              >
                octl
              </code>
               auto-installs Podman, builds dev images for every Olympus repo, brings up infra → Ory → apps → seed in order, and hands you working URLs and a test login.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div
            data-testid="terminal"
            data-title="~/Olympus · octl"
          >
            $ npm install -g @olympusoss/octl
$ octl

→ checking Podman, podman-compose, kubectl…
→ starting Podman machine
→ building dev images  (platform · hera · athena · site)
→ bringing up stack   infra → migrations → Ory → apps → seed

✓ kratos      
            <span
              style="color: rgb(134, 239, 172);"
            >
              healthy
            </span>
            
✓ hydra       
            <span
              style="color: rgb(134, 239, 172);"
            >
              healthy
            </span>
            
✓ hera        → http://localhost:3000
✓ athena      → http://localhost:3001
✓ site        → http://localhost:2000

test user → 
            <span
              style="color: rgb(165, 180, 252);"
            >
              admin@olympus.local
            </span>
             / olympus

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
